{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6151e863a07b5de5dd2bf03e", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9a"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "10", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "In between two point charges a conducting spherical shell having charge <math> <mtext>Q</mtext> </math> is placed as shown in the diagram. Assuming all charges to be positive, mark out the correct statement.<br />\r<br />\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <u><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/jee_main/images/EM0022407_Question_1.jpg\" /></strong></u>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "EfI5C", "text": "the charge on outer surface of shell is uniformly distributed", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "yOOnu", "text": "the charge on outer surface of shell is non-uniformly distributed", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "9eYIl", "text": "the information is insufficient to find the nature of charge distribution on the outer surface", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "RjMLH", "text": "none of these&nbsp;", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "To solve this question we have to use the concept that \"the resultant electric field at any point inside a conducting shell due to all outside charges is zero, \" and that \"E at any internal point due to uniformly charged conducting spherical shell is zero.\"<br />Consider any point P